Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses large-scale data centers and proposes an algorithm to reduce log data, which is relevant to distributed computing.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper focuses on improving the performance debugging of multi-tier services, which is a software engineering problem.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The proposed algorithm is a data structure and algorithmic solution to filter out valueless logs.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper may involve programming languages used in multi-tier services and their logging mechanisms.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper may involve networking and internet architecture aspects of multi-tier services and their request tracing.
